Of this last piece, however, it should be stated that it first appeared in the Remains (1648), and that, as it is described in the Harleian MS.¹⁷ as by Mr. Bacon, it must have been written before the summer of 1603. Thus, it may possibly (though I have no positive reason for saying that it is so) enter into more minute details of doctrine than Bacon would afterwards have been disposed to do. To the Christian Paradoxes I do not refer, as being now known to have been written by another hand¹⁸.
